      "name": "CFD hemolysis sensitivity validation — numerical simulation sweep",
      "description": "Validation of the CFD hemolysis model was performed by executing a parametric numerical simulation sweep across 5 flow-speed combinations (2–6 L/min, 2000–4000 RPM) representative of CPB operating conditions. The simulation results demonstrate that the model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating points and that predicted RH values remain below 1.0 across all evaluated configurations. The simulation methodology is considered equivalent to experimental validation for the purposes of this assessment because the CFD solver has been previously benchmarked against FDA flow loop data; the numerical approach is therefore argued to be 'as good as' a dedicated experiment for this COU. Predicted RH ranged from 0.41 to 0.87 across all operating points.",
